Reasoning: The paper uses science of science techniques based on complex networks to analyze the organization and interconnection between two important issues in chemistry, namely mass spectrometry (MS) and capillary electrophoresis (CE). This involves analyzing a citation network in which the nodes and connections represent papers and citations, respectively. The paper also discusses the use of multi-scale analysis to better understand the organization of the citation network. Based on this, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DL (Digital Libraries), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.DB (Databases), and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
